5181.cms%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fm.timesofindia.com%2Fworld%2Fus%2Fauthorities-say-multiple-people-believed-shot-at-california-bar%2Famp_articleshow%2F103005181.cms%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22G20%20Countries%20Spent%20a%20Record%20%24%201.4%20Trillion%20on%20Fossil%20Fuels%20in%202022%3A%20Report%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F24091507%2F32723706897_91febce798_c.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Last%20year%2C%20G20%20countries%20supported%20fossil%20fuels%20in%20a%20big%20way.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%202022%2C%20they%20spent%20a%20record%20US%20%24%201.4%20trillion%20%E2%80%93%20more%20than%20double%20the%20pre-COVID%20and%20pre-energy%20crisis%20levels%20of%202019%20%E2%80%93%20on%20fossil%20fuels%2C%20per%20a%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.iisd.org%2Fpublications%2Freport%2Ffanning-flames-g20-support-of-fossil-fuels%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ereport%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20released%20on%20August%2023%20by%20the%20International%20Institute%20for%20Sustainable%20Development%2C%20an%20international%20think%20tank.%20This%20came%20mostly%20in%20the%20form%20of%20subsidies%20(around%20US%20%24%201%20trillion)%2C%20and%20investments%20by%20state-owned%20enterprises%20and%20lending%20from%20public%20financial%20institutions.%20The%20support%20for%20fossil%20fuels%20is%20in%20contradiction%20with%20pledges%20that%20countries%20have%20made%20to%20phase%20down%20fossil%20fuels%20as%20per%20some%20international%20climate%20commitments%2C%20including%20a%20commitment%20by%20the%20G20%20in%202009.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20report%20also%20gave%20several%20recommendations%20to%20the%20G20%2C%20including%20the%20benefits%20of%20levying%20a%20carbon%20tax%20to%20incentivize%20consumers%20and%20investors%20to%20shift%20away%20from%20using%20and%20funding%20fossil%20fuels.%20Per%20their%20estimate%2C%20such%20a%20tax%20can%20bring%20in%20around%20US%20%24%201%20trillion%20every%20year%20and%20help%20finance%20social%20welfare%20schemes%20and%20just%20transitions.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20report%20comes%20ahead%20of%20the%2018th%20G20%20Leaders%E2%80%99%20Summit%20that%20will%20be%20held%20in%20September%20in%20New%20Delhi%2C%20where%20topics%20including%20climate%20change%20and%20energy%20will%20be%20discussed%3B%20all%20eyes%20are%20now%20on%20these%20talks.%20However%2C%20related%20ministerial%20and%20working%20group%20meetings%20that%20have%20concluded%20as%20part%20of%20the%20G20%20summit%20in%20India%20have%20been%20marked%20by%20a%20lack%20of%20consensus%20on%20issues%20including%20those%20pertaining%20to%20energy%20transitions.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3ERecord%20spending%20on%20fossil%20fuels%20in%202022%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAs%20per%20a%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.iisd.org%2Fpublications%2Freport%2Ffanning-flames-g20-support-of-fossil-fuels%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ereport%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20released%20August%2023%20by%20the%20International%20Institute%20for%20Sustainable%20Development%20(IISD)%2C%20G20%20countries%20spent%20a%20record%20US%20%24%201.4%20trillion%20%E2%80%93%20more%20than%20double%20the%20pre-COVID%20and%20pre-energy%20crisis%20levels%20of%202019%20%E2%80%93%20on%20fossil%20fuels.%20This%20came%20mostly%20in%20the%20form%20of%20subsidies%20which%20amounted%20to%20at%20least%20US%20%24%201%20trillion.%20Per%20the%20report%2C%20this%20was%20more%20than%20four%20times%20the%20annual%20average%20in%20the%20previous%20decade%2C%20and%20due%20to%20the%20high%20consumption%20subsidies%20that%20countries%20offered%20in%20response%20to%20the%20energy%20crisis%20fuelled%20by%20the%20ongoing%20Russia-Ukraine%20war.%20It%20is%20crucial%20that%20G20%20countries%20agree%20to%20a%20deadline%20to%20eliminate%20fossil%20fuel%20subsidies%20(such%20as%20the%20G7%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theguardian.com%2Fenvironment%2F2016%2Fmay%2F27%2Fg7-nations-pledge-to-end-fossil-fuel-subsidies-by-2025%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ecommitting%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20to%20doing%20this%20by%202025).%20Removing%20subsidies%20could%20also%20save%20thousands%20of%20lives%20by%20reducing%20fossil%20fuel-related%20air%20pollution%2C%20which%20is%20responsible%20for%20over%205%20million%20deaths%20per%20year%20in%20G20%20countries%20and%20one%20in%20five%20deaths%20globally%2C%20per%20the%20report.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F06%2F16203251%2FDelhi-G20.jpeg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F06%2F16203251%2FDelhi-G20.jpeg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F06%2F16203251%2FDelhi-G20-300x186.jpeg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F06%2F16203251%2FDelhi-G20-1024x636.jpeg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-658633%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22745%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EG20%20posters%20are%20often%20seen%20in%20Delhi%20as%20the%20city%20is%20set%20to%20host%20the%20summit%20in%20September%20this%20year.%20Photo%3A%20Twitter%2F%40sidhant.%20February%2028%2C%202023.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EInvestments%20in%20fossil%20fuel%20infrastructure%20by%20state-owned%20enterprises%20(SOEs)%20in%20G20%20countries%20was%20also%20above%20pre-pandemic%20and%20pre-energy%20crisis%20levels%2C%20at%20US%20%24%20322%20billion%20in%202022%2C%20per%20the%20report.%20Such%20investments%2C%20%E2%80%9Ca%20massive%20down%20payment%20on%20new%20fossil%20production%2C%20GHG%20emissions%2C%20and%20pollution%E2%80%9D%2C%20are%20also%20increasing%2C%20and%20this%20is%20%E2%80%9Cstarkly%20at%20odds%E2%80%9D%20with%20the%20latest%20climate%20science%20that%20suggests%20that%20countries%20should%20not%20invest%20in%20setting%20up%20new%20fossil%20fuel%20supply%20projects%2C%20it%20said.%20Citing%20the%20example%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20NTPC%20(formerly%20the%20National%20Thermal%20Power%20Corporation)%2C%20the%20report%20recommended%20that%20SOEs%20%E2%80%9Cdevelop%20and%20implement%20evidence-based%20diversification%20strategies%20that%20identify%20new%20clean%20energy%20business%20opportunities%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhile%20international%20public%20financing%20for%20fossil%20fuels%20has%20been%20decreasing%2C%20and%20is%20still%20at%20an%20average%20of%20US%20%24%2050%20billion%20per%20year%20(from%202019%20to%202021)%2C%20it%E2%80%99s%20still%20not%20enough.%20It%20is%20still%20nearly%20four%20times%20greater%20than%20support%20for%20clean%20energy%2C%20the%20report%20noted.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3ERenewable%20energy%20and%20a%20carbon%20tax%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EGlobal%20investment%20in%20renewable%20energy%20reached%20a%20record%20high%20of%20US%20%24%20500%20billion%20in%202022%20but%20was%20still%20only%20around%20half%20of%20the%20investment%20in%20fossil%20fuels%20(US%20%24%20950%20billion)%2C%20the%20report%20found.%20While%20G20%20countries%20announced%20US%20%24%20265%20billion%20in%20subsidies%20for%20renewable%20power%20generation%20between%202020%20and%20June%202023%2C%20subsidies%20for%20fossil%20fuels%20were%20far%20higher%2C%20amounting%20to%20over%20US%20%24%201.4%20trillion%20from%202020%20to%202022.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20report%20recommends%20that%20the%20G20%20countries%20act%20on%20climate%20commitments%20by%20eliminating%20all%20public%20financial%20flows%20to%20fossil%20fuels%20other%20than%20those%20necessary%20to%20provide%20energy%20access%20to%20the%20poorest.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20boldest%2C%20fastest%20action%20should%20be%20from%20the%20G20%E2%80%99s%20highest%20per-capita%20income%20members%2C%20given%20their%20historical%20responsibility%20for%20emissions%20and%20higher%20emissions%20per%20unit%20of%20GDP%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20report%20said.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20IISD%20report%20also%20recommends%20that%20the%20G20%20incentivise%20consumers%20and%20investors%20to%20shift%20away%20from%20fossil%20fuels%20by%20setting%20minimum%20carbon%20taxation%20levels%20of%20between%20US%20%24%2025%20and%20US%20%24%2075%20per%20tonne%20of%20carbon%20dioxide%20equivalent%20(tCO2e)%2C%20depending%20on%20country%20income.%20This%2C%20they%20say%2C%20will%20bring%20in%20at%20least%20US%20%24%201%20trillion%20every%20year%2C%20and%20can%20be%20used%20to%20fund%20important%20social%20welfare%20schemes%20and%20just%20transition%20in%20these%20countries.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20report%20provides%20%E2%80%9Cimpactful%20numbers%E2%80%9D%20and%20tells%20a%20%E2%80%9Cvery%20alarming%20story%E2%80%9D%2C%20commented%20Diala%20Hawila%2C%20programme%20officer%2C%20International%20Renewable%20Energy%20Agency.%20It%20shows%20how%20dwarfed%20renewable%20energy%20investments%20are%20when%20compared%20to%20fossil%20fuels%2C%20especially%20when%20we%20look%20at%20public%20investments%2C%20she%20said.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2018%2F11%2F21154443%2FThinkstockPhotos-854613344.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221020%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2018%2F11%2F21154443%2FThinkstockPhotos-854613344.jpg%201020w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2018%2F11%2F21154443%2FThinkstockPhotos-854613344-300x200.jpg%20300w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-313321%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22680%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20IISD%20report%20also%20recommends%20that%20the%20G20%20incentivise%20consumers%20and%20investors%20to%20shift%20away%20from%20fossil%20fuels%20by%20setting%20minimum%20carbon%20taxation%20levels.%20Photo%3C%2Fspan%3E%3A%20Thinkstock%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20findings%20of%20the%20report%20suggest%20that%20the%20support%20for%20fossil%20fuels%20by%20the%20G20%20in%202022%20is%20in%20contradiction%20to%20the%20pledges%20of%20phasing%20down%20fossil%20fuels%20that%20countries%20have%20made%20as%20per%20some%20international%20climate%20commitments%2C%20including%20a%20commitment%20by%20the%20G20%20in%202009.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20report%20recommended%20that%20G20%20members%20set%20a%20clear%20deadline%20%E2%80%93%202025%20for%20developed%20countries%20and%202030%20for%20emerging%20economies%20%E2%80%93%20to%20eliminate%20fossil%20fuel%20subsidies%20and%20deliver%20on%20their%202009%20commitment%20to%20reform%20subsidies.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20would%20like%20the%20G20%20to%20show%20some%20leadership%20here%20and%20push%20the%20level%20of%20ambition%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Tara%20Laan%2C%20senior%20associate%2C%20IISD%2C%20and%20the%20lead%20author%20of%20the%20report.%20This%20is%20particularly%20important%20because%20the%20Conference%20of%20Parties%20is%20coming%20up%20and%20the%20G20%20cannot%20be%20seen%20in%20isolation%20of%20that%2C%20she%20added.%20%E2%80%9CThis%20COP%20is%20controversial%20and%20we%E2%80%99re%20concerned%20that%20the%20level%20of%20ambition%20will%20not%20be%20high%20given%20where%20it%20is%20being%20hosted%E2%80%A6there%20are%20strong%20fossil%20fuel%20interests%20there.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fenvironment%2Flack-of-unanimity-on-climate-targets-among-g20-delegates%5C%22%3ELack%20of%20Unanimity%20on%20Climate%20Targets%20Among%20G20%20Delegates%20Worries%20COP%20Organisers%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20United%20Arab%20Emirates%20will%20host%20the%2028th%20Conference%20of%20Parties%20(COP28)%20at%20Dubai%20later%20this%20year.%20The%20COP%E2%80%99s%20President-Designate%2C%20Sultan%20Ahmed%20Al%20Jaber%2C%20is%20the%20UAE%E2%80%99s%20Minister%20of%20Industry%20and%20Advanced%20Technology%20and%20the%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fenvironment%2Fuae-oil-company-adnoc-ceo-cop28-president%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eserving%20CEO%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20of%20the%20United%20Arab%20Emirates-owned%20Abu%20Dhabi%20National%20Oil%20Company.%20The%20company%20was%20able%20to%20read%20emails%20to%20and%20from%20the%20CoP28%20climate%20summit%20office%20and%20was%20consulted%20on%20how%20to%20respond%20to%20a%20media%20inquiry%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Guardian%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theguardian.com%2Fenvironment%2F2023%2Fjun%2F07%2Fuae-oil-firm-cop28-climate-summit-emails-sultan-al-jaber-adnoc%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ereported%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20in%20June.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EIndia%2C%20fossil%20fuels%20and%20the%20G20%20summit%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CAs%20G20%20chair%2C%20India%20can%20confidently%20demonstrate%20global%20leadership%20in%20this%20area%2C%20having%20reduced%20its%20fossil%20fuel%20subsidies%20by%2076%25%20from%202014%20to%202022%20while%20significantly%20increasing%20support%20for%20clean%20energy%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20report%20said.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F11%2F01113927%2FUntitled-design-13.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22G20%20summit%202021%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F11%2F01113927%2FUntitled-design-13.png%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F11%2F01113927%2FUntitled-design-13-300x150.png%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F11%2F01113927%2FUntitled-design-13-1024x512.png%201024w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F11%2F01113927%2FUntitled-design-13-800x400.png%20800w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-561723%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22600%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EPrime%20Minister%20Modi%20at%20an%20earlier%20session%20of%20the%20G20%20Summit%20in%20Rome%20on%20climate%20change.%20Photo%3A%20PTI%2FFile%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHowever%2C%20the%20meetings%20that%20have%20concluded%20do%20not%20offer%20much%20hope.%20The%20G20%20Environment%20and%20Climate%20Ministers%E2%80%99%20Meeting%20that%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fenvironment%2Fg20-environment-ministers-meet-concludes-lack-of-consensus-on-emissions-other-crucial-issues%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Econcluded%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20on%20July%2028%20in%20Chennai%2C%20for%20instance%2C%20was%20marked%20by%20a%20lack%20of%20consensus%20on%20emissions%2C%20and%20other%20crucial%20issues.%20Per%20the%20outcome%20document%2C%20despite%20discussions%20on%20the%20importance%20of%20clean%20energy%20transitions%2C%20including%20accelerating%20the%20scaling%20up%20of%20renewable%20energy%2C%20tripling%20renewable%20capacity%2C%20and%20phasing%20down%20fossil%20fuels%2C%20there%20existed%20%E2%80%9Cdivergent%20views%E2%80%9D%20among%20members%20to%20discuss%20energy%20issues%20in%20light%20of%20the%20existence%20of%20a%20separate%20Energy%20Transition%20Working%20Group.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWe%20expect%20to%20see%20the%20G20%20show%20leadership%20in%20urgently%20implementing%20a%20shift%20in%20public%20financial%20flows%20away%20from%20fossil%20fuels%2C%20said%20Shruti%20Sharma%2C%20senior%20policy%20advisor%2C%20IISD%2C%20in%20reply%20to%20questions%20at%20the%20online%20launch%20of%20the%20report%20on%20August%2023.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20%E2%80%98recommend%E2%80%99%20G20%20members%20to%20improve%20transparency%20%E2%80%9Ccommit%20to%20annually%20report%20on%20all%20support%20for%20fossil%20fuels%20under%20indicator%20SDG%2012.c.1%2C%20in%20a%20comprehensive%20manner%20and%20on%20an%20annual%20basis%E2%80%9D%E2%80%9D%2C%20she%20wrote.%20%E2%80%9CWe%20also%20recommend%20and%20expect%20G20%20members%20to%20adopt%20a%20specific%20timeline%20for%20fossil-fuel%20subsidy%20reform%2C%20bearing%20in%20mind%20the%20G7%20goal%20to%20phase%20out%20fossil%20fuel%20subsidies%20by%202025%2C%20and%20the%20need%20to%20show%20leadership%20by%20fully%20implementing%20reforms%20before%202030.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIndia%2C%20she%20said%2C%20has%20a%20strong%20track%20record%20on%20reform%20implementation%20because%20it%20reduced%20the%20value%20of%20fossil%20fuel%20subsidies%20by%2076%25%20between%202014%20and%202022.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CSo%20there%E2%80%99s%20a%20real%20opportunity%20for%20the%20Presidency%20to%20bring%20it%20up%20in%20this%20year%E2%80%99s%20agenda%2C%E2%80%9D%20Sharma%20said.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAll%20eyes%20are%20now%20on%20the%20G20%20World%20Leaders%E2%80%99%20Summit%20that%20will%20take%20place%20in%20New%20Delhi%20on%20September%209%20and%2010.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1692849763000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F24091507%2F32723706897_91febce798_c.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fenvironment%2Fg20-countries-trillion-fossil-fuel%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20report%20by%20an%20international%20think%20tank%20comes%20ahead%20of%20the%2018th%20G20%20world%20leaders%E2%80%99%20summit%20that%20will%20be%20held%20in%20September%20in%20New%20Delhi%2C%20where%20discussions%20will%20also%20revolve%20around%20climate%20change%20and%20energy.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fenvironment%2Fg20-countries-trillion-fossil-fuel%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Stock%20Market%20LIVE%3A%20Sensex%20up%20350pts%2C%20Nifty%20above%2019%2C500%3B%20Metal%20stocks%20shine%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1692849713000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fbsmedia.business-standard.com%2F_media%2Fbs%2Fimg%2Farticle%2F2022-12%2F26%2Ffull%2F1672027506-0538.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Fmarkets%2Fnews%2Fstock-market-live-august-23-nse-bse-sensex-today-nifty-rupee-treasury-yields-share-market-updates-123082400097_1.html%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Stock%20Market%20Updates%20LIVE%3A%20Broader%20markets%2C%20too%2C%20exhibited%20strength%20as%20Nifty%20Midcap%20100%20and%20Nifty%20Smallcap%20100%20indices%20rose%20up%20to%200.7%20per%20cent%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Fmarkets%2Fnews%2Fstock-market-live-august-23-nse-bse-sensex-today-nifty-rupee-treasury-yields-share-market-updates-123082400097_1.html%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-business--standard-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Famp%2Fmarkets%2Fnews%2Fstock-market-live-august-23-nse-bse-sensex-today-nifty-rupee-treasury-yields-share-market-updates-123082400097_1.html%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Famp%2Fmarkets%2Fnews%2Fstock-market-live-august-23-nse-bse-sensex-today-nifty-rupee-treasury-yields-share-market-updates-123082400097_1.html%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22As%20India%20Celebrates%20Chandrayaan-3%2C%20A%20Faux%20Pas%20By%20Mamata%20Banerjee%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EWhile%20India%20celebrated%20the%20historic%20achievement%20of%20the%20Chandrayaan-3%20moon%20mission%20landing%20on%20the%20lunar%20south%20pole%20on%20Wednesday%2C%20West%20Bengal%20Chief%20Minister%20Mamata%20Banerjee's%20faux%20pas%20has%20become%20a%20subject%20of%20ridicule.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESpeaking%20at%20an%20event%20in%20Kolkata%20shortly%20before%20the%20Chandrayaan-3%20lander%20reached%20the%20moon%2C%20Chief%20Minister%20Banerjee%20confused%20astronaut%20Rakesh%20Sharma%20with%20Bollywood%20actor-filmmaker%20Rakesh%20Roshan.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOn%20behalf%20of%20the%20people%20of%20West%20Bengal%2C%20I%20send%20my%20advance%20congratulations%20to%20ISRO.%20Scientists%20must%20get%20credit.%20Credit%20must%20go%20to%20the%20country.%20When%20Rakesh%20Roshan%20%5Bsic%5D%20landed%20on%20the%20moon%2C%20former%20Prime%20Minister%20Indira%20Gandhi%20asked%20him%20how%20India%20looked%20from%20there%2C%26quot%3B%20Ms%20Banerjee%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERakesh%20Sharma%2C%20an%20Indian%20Air%20Force%20pilot%20became%20the%20first%20Indian%20to%20travel%20to%20space%20in%201984%20as%20part%20of%20the%20Soviet%20Union's%20Soyuz%20T-11%20expedition.%20The%20astronaut%20spoke%20to%20then-Prime%20Minister%20Indira%20Gandhi%20from%20space%20during%20a%20live%20televised%20news%20conference.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndira%20Gandhi%20asked%20Mr%20Sharma%2C%20%26quot%3BUpar%20se%20Bharat%20kaisa%20dikhta%20hai%20aapko%3F%26quot%3B%20(How%20does%20India%20look%20like%20from%20space%3F).%20He%20responded%20by%20quoting%20the%20poet%20Iqbal%20and%20saying%2C%20%26quot%3BSaare%20jahaan%20se%20achcha%26quot%3B%20(Better%20than%20the%20whole%20world).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20West%20Bengal%20Chief%20Minister's%20gaffe%20went%20viral%20on%20social%20media%2C%20triggering%20thousands%20of%20memes%20at%20her%20expense.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EStrangely%2C%20Ms%20Banerjee%20was%20not%20the%20only%20politician%20to%20be%20involved%20in%20a%20Chandrayaan-3-related%20goof-up.%20On%20the%20other%20side%20of%20the%20country%2C%20a%20Rajasthan%20minister%20congratulated%20the%20%26quot%3Bpassengers%26quot%3B%20of%20the%20Chandrayaan-3%20mission%20despite%20the%20fact%20that%20it%20is%20an%20unmanned%20mission.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20we%20are%20successful%20and%20make%20a%20safe%20landing%2C%20I%20salute%20the%20passengers%2C%20Our%20country%20has%20taken%20a%20step%20further%20in%20science%20and%20space%20research.%20I%20congratulate%20the%20countrymen%20for%20this%2C%26quot%3B%20Rajasthan%20Sports%20Minister%20Ashok%20Chandna%20said%20as%20quoted%20by%20news%20agency%20PTI.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndia%20made%20history%20by%20becoming%20the%20first%20country%20to%20land%20a%20spacecraft%20near%20the%20moon's%20south%20pole%2C%20a%20region%20that%20is%20thought%20to%20contain%20water%20ice.%20The%20touchdown%20took%20place%20at%206%3A04%20pm%20on%20Wednesday%20and%20was%20met%20with%20cheers%20and%20celebrations%20at%20the%20ISRO%20headquarters%20in%20Bengaluru.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20rover%20Pragyan%20will%20explore%20the%20lunar%20surface%20for%20the%20next%2014%20days%2C%20or%20one%20lunar%20day%2C%20sending%20back%20images%20and%20data%20to%20scientists%20on%20Earth.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1692849300000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-08%2Ftc8b0jl8_mamata-banerjee_625x300_22_August_23.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fchandrayaan-3-rakesh-roshan-rakesh-sharma-as-india-celebrates-chandrayaan-3-a-faux-pas-by-mamata-banerjee-4324438%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22While%20India%20celebrated%20the%20historic%20achievement%20of%20the%20Chandrayaan-3%20moon%20mission%20landing%20on%20the%20lunar%20s