%3EIn%201997%2C%20a%20lone%20wolf%20crossed%20an%20ice%20bridge%20that%20briefly%20connected%20Canada%20with%20the%20remote%20Isle%20Royale%2C%20which%20lies%20off%20the%20coast%20of%20Michigan%20in%20Lake%20Superior%20and%20is%20renowned%20for%20its%20rich%20biodiversity.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHis%20arrival%20revived%20the%20flagging%20fortunes%20of%20the%20wider%20wolf%20population%2C%20which%20had%20been%20hit%20by%20disease%20and%20inbreeding%2C%20and%20triggered%20cascading%20effects%20that%20improved%20the%20health%20of%20the%20overall%20forest%20ecosystem%2C%20a%20study%20in%20Science%20Advances%20showed%20Wednesday.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIssues%20like%20inbreeding%20and%20low%20genetic%20diversity%20are%20an%20important%20concern%20for%20scientists%2C%26quot%3B%20first%20author%20Sarah%20Hoy%2C%20an%20ecologist%20at%20Michigan%20Technological%20University%20told%20AFP.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBut%20this%20is%20the%20first%20study%20that%20shows%20when%20you%20have%20these%20genetic%20issues%2C%20they%20don't%20just%20impact%20the%20particular%20population%20and%20increase%20the%20risk%20that%20they%20will%20go%20extinct%3A%20they%20also%20have%20these%20really%20big%20knock%20on%20effects%20on%20all%20the%20other%20species.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E'Old%20Gray%20Guy'%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20first%20wolves%20arrived%20on%20the%20island%20in%20the%20late%201940s%2C%20and%20their%20main%20prey%20are%20moose%20--%20giving%20rise%20to%20the%20longest%20running%20study%20of%20a%20predator-prey%20system%20anywhere%20in%20the%20world.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20by%20the%201980s%2C%20the%20wolves%20were%20in%20trouble%20due%20to%20the%20arrival%20of%20canine%20parvovirus%20which%20drove%20their%20numbers%20down%20from%20a%20high%20of%2050%20to%20around%2012.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThough%20the%20disease%20eventually%20disappeared%2C%20the%20population%20didn't%20recover%20right%20away.%20The%20reason%20was%20severe%20inbreeding%2C%20which%20caused%20lower%20reproductive%20success%2C%20as%20well%20as%20poorer%20health%20outcomes%20such%20as%20spinal%20deformities%20of%20the%20kind%20often%20seen%20in%20purebred%20dogs.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20you're%20a%20wild%20wolf%20and%20you're%20having%20to%20take%20down%20prey%20like%20a%20moose%20that's%20eight%20times%20your%20size%2C%20that%20can%20make%20life%20in%20the%20wild%20really%20tough%20for%20you%2C%26quot%3B%20Hoy%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEnter%20the%20immigrant%2C%20identified%20as%20%26quot%3BM93%26quot%3B%20by%20scientists%2C%20but%20affectionately%20nicknamed%20%26quot%3BThe%20Old%20Gray%20Guy.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EM93%20was%20unrelated%20to%20the%20existing%20population%2C%20and%20also%20had%20the%20advantage%20of%20being%20unusually%20large%20--%20a%20big%20benefit%20when%20defending%20turf%20from%20rivals%20or%20taking%20down%20800%20pound%20ungulates.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20quickly%20became%20the%20breeding%20male%20in%20one%20of%20the%20island's%20three%20wolf%20packs%20and%20went%20on%20to%20sire%2034%20pups%2C%20greatly%20improving%20the%20genetic%20health%20of%20the%20population%20and%20the%20kill%20rate%20of%20its%20prey.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ERestoring%20balance%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMoose%20are%20voracious%20herbivores%2C%20consuming%20up%20to%2030%20pounds%20(14%20kilograms)%20of%20vegetation%20a%20day.%20By%20reducing%20their%20numbers%2C%20the%20wolves%20helped%20bring%20the%20forest%20back%20into%20balance%2C%20which%20was%20most%20notable%20in%20the%20effects%20on%20balsam%20firs%20--%20the%20species%20commonly%20used%20as%20Christmas%20trees.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWith%20fewer%20moose%2C%20the%20trees%20began%20growing%20at%20rates%20not%20seen%20in%20decades%2C%20which%20is%20vital%20for%20the%20renewal%20of%20the%20forest%20and%20the%20myriad%20plant%20and%20animal%20species%20that%20depend%20on%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20benefits%20brought%20by%20M93's%20arrival%20lasted%20around%20a%20decade%2C%20then%20the%20situation%20deteriorated%20once%20more%20--%20ironically%20as%20a%20result%20of%20his%20extreme%20reproductive%20success.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBy%202008%2C%20two%20years%20after%20his%20death%2C%2060%20percent%20of%20the%20wolf%20population's%20gene%20pool%20was%20inherited%20from%20M93%2C%20which%20led%20to%20a%20return%20of%20genetic%20deterioration.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EM93%20himself%20began%20breeding%20with%20his%20daughter%20after%20his%20mate%20died%2C%20and%20simultaneous%20inbreeding%20by%20other%20members%20triggered%20a%20rapid%20population%20decline%20until%202015%2C%20when%20there%20were%20just%20two%20wolves%20left%3A%20a%20father-daughter%20pair%20who%20were%20also%20half%20siblings.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFortunately%2C%20a%20restoration%20program%20beginning%20in%202018%20has%20once%20more%20brought%20balance%20to%20the%20system%2C%20and%20there%20are%20currently%20around%2030%20wolves%20and%20just%20under%20a%20thousand%20moose%20on%20the%20island.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20Hoy%2C%20a%20key%20takeaway%20is%20that%20the%20same%20principle%20of%20inserting%20just%20a%20small%20number%20of%20individuals%20could%20be%20applied%20to%20other%20imperiled%20predator%20populations%20that%20suffer%20from%20the%20harmful%20effects%20of%20inbreeding%2C%20such%20as%20lions%20or%20cheetahs%2C%20to%20similarly%20improve%20their%20ecosystems.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWilliam%20Ripple%2C%20a%20professor%20of%20ecology%20at%20Oregon%20State%20University%20who%20was%20not%20part%20of%20the%20research%2C%20told%20AFP%20it%20was%20an%20%26quot%3Bimportant%20study%26quot%3B%20that%20advances%20understanding%20%26quot%3Bby%20showing%20that%20genetic%20processes%20may%20limit%20the%20ecological%20effects%20of%20a%20keystone%20species%2C%20the%20gray%20wolf.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E(This%20story%20has%20not%20been%20edited%20by%20NDTV%20staff%20and%20is%20auto-generated%20from%20a%20syndicated%20feed.)%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%2