%20second%20game%20of%20Classical%20Chess%20at%20the%20Federation%20Internationale%20des%20Echecs%20(FIDE)%20World%20Cup%20final%20between%20Indian%20grandmaster%20R%20Praggnanandhaa%20and%20Norway's%20world%20number%20one%20Magnus%20Carlsen%20ended%20in%20a%20draw%20on%20Wednesday%2C%20with%20the%20winner%20of%20the%20tournament%20set%20to%20be%20decided%20on%20Thursday.%20The%20contest%20between%20these%20two%20Chess%20stars%20has%20now%20moved%20to%20tie-breakers.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BToday%2C%20Carlsen%20had%20white%20pieces%20and%20Praggnanandhaa%20had%20black.%20Magnus%20could%20have%20been%20aggressive%20and%20taken%20his%20chances.%20But%20he%20did%20not.%20It%20is%20a%20great%20feat%20for%20our%20young%20Turk%20Prag%20(Praggnanandhaa).%20When%20you%20see%20a%20young%20player%20like%20him%20do%20so%20well%2C%20draw%20games%20against%20Magnus%2C%20it%20means%20that%20he%20is%20playing%20on%20par%20with%20him%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20the%20AICF%20chief%20in%20an%20interview%20with%20ANI.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20India's%20performance%20in%20the%20FIDE%20Chess%20World%20Cup%2C%20Sanjay%20said%20that%20India's%20chess%20future%20is%20bright.%20Notably%2C%20four%20out%20of%20eight%20quarterfinalists%20this%20time%20around%20were%20Indians.%20This%20included%20Praggnanandhaa%2C%20Gukesh%20D%2C%20Vidit%20Gujrathi%20and%20Arjun%20Erigaisi.%20While%20Gukesh%20lost%20to%20Carlsen%20and%20Vidit%20lost%20to%20Nijat%20Abasov%20of%20Azerbaijan%2C%20Praggnanandhaa%20defeated%20Arjun%20to%20reach%20the%20semis%2C%20where%20he%20beat%20Fabiano%20Caruana%20of%20the%20US.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20the%20Olympiad%20last%20year%2C%20we%20had%20the%20podium%20finish%20in%20both%20men's%20and%20women's%20team%20events%20(Bronze%20medal%20in%20both%20categories).%20It%20has%20never%20happened%20before.%20Now%20our%20young%20Turks%20have%20started%20to%20show%20the%20results.%20India%20has%20started%20showing%20great%20results%20after%20a%20long%20time.%20Everyone%20knows%20our%20champion%2C%20Vishy%20(Vishwanathan%20Anand)%2C%20but%20now%20I%20feel%20that%20our%20Chess%20future%20is%20bright.%20Superb%20performance%20by%20them%2C%20great%20admiration%20for%20all%20who%20went%20to%20the%20quarterfinals.%20Losing%20or%20winning%20one%20game%20does%20not%20define%20you.%20Having%20four%20out%20of%20eight%20quarterfinalists%20as%20Indians%20is%20a%20matter%20of%20pride%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Sanjay.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETalking%20about%20his%20relationship%20with%20the%2018-year-old%20Chess%20prodigy%2C%20Sanjay%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BFor%20me%2C%20he%20is%20my%20son.%20He%20is%20a%20good%20child.%20Every%20time%20I%20see%20him%2C%20I%20feel%20like%20hugging%20him.%20You%20cannot%20explain%20that%20feeling.%20His%20mother%20and%20father%20feel%20really%20happy%20when%20they%20see%20me.%20Whenever%20I%20come%20to%20meet%20him%2C%20I%20ask%20him%20if%20he%20wants%20something%2C%20he%20says%20that%20'you%20are%20here%2C%20that%20is%20all'.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20tie-breaker%20scheduled%20for%20Thursday%2C%20the%20AICF%20chief%20said%20that%20Praggnanandhaa%20should%20win%2C%20for%20the%20nation%2C%20for%20its%20chess%20players%20and%20Prime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi%2C%20whom%20he%20credited%20for%20%26quot%3Bblessing%20the%20Indian%20chess%26quot%3B.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BHe%20(Praggnanandhaa)%20will%20win%2C%20no%20second%20thoughts%2C%20no%20second%20questions%20asked.%20I%20want%20him%20to%20win.%20He%20is%20our%20country's%20son%2C%20he%20should%20win.%C2%A0%20Our%20PM%20has%20a%20golden%20touch%2C%20a%20way%20to%20motivate%20others.%20It%20is%20because%20of%20him%20that%20we%20are%20doing%20so%20well.%20When%20you%20meet%20him%2C%20you%20feel%20energised.%20The%20face%20of%20Indian%20chess%20has%20changed%20ever%20since%20he%20gave%20it%20his%20blessings.%20So%20we%20have%20to%20win%20it%20for%20him%2C%20for%20such%20a%20dynamic%20PM%2C%20for%20every%20Indian%20and%20for%20every%20chess%20player%20in%20this%20country%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20concluded.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECarlsen%20drew%20the%20first%20game%20of%20classical%20chess%20after%2035%20moves%20with%20the%20Indian%20prodigy.%20In%20case%20the%20second%20game%20ended%20in%20a%20tie%2C%20the%20players%20would%20have%20moved%20to%20two%20games%20of%20Rapid%20Chess%20to%20decide%20the%20winner%20of%20this%20year's%20Chess%20World%20Cup%20final%20being%20played%20at%20Baku%2C%20Azerbaijan.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPraggnanandhaa%C2%A0started%20on%20a%20strong%20note%20with%20white%20pieces%20and%20enjoyed%20a%20time%20advantage%20over%20the%20Norwegian%20in%20the%20initial%20phase.%20Carlsen%20managed%20to%20bounce%20back%20against%20a%20player%20who%20seemed%20to%20be%20well-versed%20with%20the%20lines%20and%20moves%20the%20Norwegian%20was%20going%20to%20opt%20for.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBoth%20Grandmasters%20continued%20their%20play%20in%20the%20second%20classical%20game%20on%20Wednesday%2C%20in%20which%20Magnus%20had%20white%20pieces.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20defeating%20World%20No%203%20Fabiano%20Caruana%20in%20tiebreaks%2C%20Praggnanandhaa%20reached%20the%20final%20to%20set%20up%20a%20clash%20with%20Carlsen.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWith%20both%20the%20classical%20chess%20games%20tied%20a%20playoff%20will%20take%20place%20on%20Thursday.%20The%20tiebreak%20procedure%20involves%20two%20rapid%20games%20with%20a%20time%20control%20of%2025%20minutes%20plus%20a%2010-second%20increment%20per%20move.%20If%20further%20resolution%20is%20required%2C%20two%20'slow%20blitz'%20games%20with%20a%20time%20control%20of%2010%20minutes%20plus%2010%20seconds%20increment%20per%20move%20follow.%20%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E(Except%20for%20the%20headline%2C%20this%20story%20has%20not%20been%20edited%20by%20NDTV%20staff%20and%20is%20published%20from%20a%20syndicated%20feed.)%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1692846480000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-08%2Fasa