aan-3-landing-melts-hearts-watch-4323752%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fsports-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fsports.ndtv.com%2Fcricket%2Fms-dhonis-daughter-zivas-reaction-on-chandrayaan-3-landing-melts-hearts-watch-4323752%2Famp%2F1%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fsports.ndtv.com%2Fcricket%2Fms-dhonis-daughter-zivas-reaction-on-chandrayaan-3-landing-melts-hearts-watch-4323752%2Famp%2F1%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22As%20BRICS%20Evolves%20Criteria%20for%20Expansion%2C%20Here%E2%80%99s%20What%20India%20Thinks%20of%20the%2022%20Countries%20That%20Want%20to%20Join%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F23224458%2FH20230823137024.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20With%20a%20large%20number%20of%20developing%20countries%20clamouring%20to%20join%20the%20BRICS%20countries%2C%20India%20is%20wary%20about%20the%20dynamics%20of%20an%20expanded%20bloc%20and%20has%20indicated%20that%20it%20will%20give%20preference%20to%20its%20%E2%80%9CStrategic%20Partners%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBRICS%20initially%20consisted%20of%20Brazil%2C%20Russia%2C%20India%2C%20and%20China%20%E2%80%93%20an%20acronym%20coined%20by%20Goldman%20Sachs%20in%20the%201990s%20to%20promote%20investment%20in%20emerging%20economies.%20South%20Africa%20was%20the%20first%20non-original%20member%20to%20join%20the%20group%2C%20making%20it%20fitting%20that%20the%20African%20nation%20chairs%20a%20summit%20focused%20on%20expanding%20the%20group.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ELast%20year%E2%80%99s%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.mea.gov.in%2Fbilateral-documents.htm%3Fdtl%2F35435%2FXIV%2BBRICS%2BSummit%2BBeijing%2BDeclaration%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EBeijing%20Declaration%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20mandated%20the%20five%20member%20states%20to%20hold%20%E2%80%9Cdiscussions%E2%80%9D%20to%20clarify%20the%20%E2%80%9Cguiding%20principles%2C%20standards%2C%20criteria%20and%20procedures%20for%20this%20expansion%20process%20through%20the%20sherpas%E2%80%99%20channel%20on%20the%20basis%20of%20full%20consultation%20and%20consensus%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAlthough%20all%20members%20have%20generally%20agreed%20to%20the%20idea%20of%20expansion%2C%20determining%20the%20criteria%20has%20involved%20prolonged%20negotiations%20due%20to%20differing%20visions%20among%20members%20regarding%20the%20group%E2%80%99s%20future%20composition.%20On%20Wednesday%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2FBenjaminNorton%2Fstatus%2F1694373757979091400%3Fs%3D20%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESouth%20Africa%E2%80%99s%20Foreign%20Minister%20Naledi%20Pandor%20said%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20the%20group%20had%20reached%20an%20agreement%20on%20the%20criteria%20and%20that%20an%20announcement%20would%20be%20made%20in%20the%20summit%E2%80%99s%20final%20declaration%20on%20Thursday.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EGiven%20the%2022%20official%20applicants%2C%20geographical%20quotas%20and%20economic%20strength%20would%20most%20likely%20also%20play%20a%20role%20in%20the%20qualification%20process.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAs%20per%20Indian%20sources%2C%20the%20BRICS%20leaders%E2%80%99%20retreat%20on%20Tuesday%20evening%20witnessed%20%E2%80%9Csignificant%20development%E2%80%9D%20on%20the%20issue%20of%20expansion.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CIndia%20took%20the%20lead%20in%20forging%20a%20consensus%20on%20membership%20criteria%20and%20the%20selection%20of%20new%20members%2C%E2%80%9D%20an%20Indian%20official%20said..%20India%E2%80%99s%20efforts%20were%20%E2%80%9Cguided%20by%20our%20objective%20to%20incorporate%20our%20Strategic%20Partners%20as%20new%20members%E2%80%9D%2C%20added%20the%20officials.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20next%20day%2C%20the%20Indian%20prime%20minister%20asserted%20at%20the%20BRICS%20plenary%20that%20India%20%E2%80%9Cfully%20supports%E2%80%9D%20expansion%2C%20adding%20that%20it%20%E2%80%9Cwelcomes%20moving%20forward%20with%20consensus%20in%20this%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EGiven%20BRICS%E2%80%99%20decision-making%20process%20is%20reliant%20on%20consensus%2C%20the%20addition%20of%20nations%20more%20inclined%20toward%20China%E2%80%99s%20perspective%20would%20be%20diplomatically%20challenging.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIndia%20has%20a%20%E2%80%98strategic%20partnership%E2%80%99%20with%20at%20least%20seven%20of%20the%20applicants%2C%20ranging%20from%20the%20UAE%20to%20Argentina%20and%20Vietnam.%20However%2C%20there%20is%20no%20clarity%20regarding%20whether%20the%20term%20%E2%80%98Strategic%20Partners%2C%E2%80%99%20as%20used%20by%20Indian%20sources%20above%2C%20pertains%20to%20the%20formal%20standing%20of%20the%20bilateral%20relationship%20or%20serves%20as%20an%20evaluation%20of%20the%20country%E2%80%99s%20significance%20to%20India.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHere%20is%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Wire%E2%80%99s%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20evaluation%20of%20how%20India%20likely%20views%20the%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22about%3Ablank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3E22%20countries%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20who%20have%20applied%20for%20membership%20to%20BRICS.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EAlgeria%C2%A0%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cem%3EIndia%E2%80%99s%20stake%3A%3C%2Fem%3E%20With%20a%20history%20of%20working%20together%20in%20the%20Non-Aligned%20Movement%20(NAM)%2C%20India%E2%80%99s%20relationship%20with%20the%20North%20African%20state%20has%20largely%20been%20free%20of%20any%20irritants.%20However%2C%20Algeria%E2%80%99s%20economic%20relationship%20with%20China%20has%20grown%20by%20leaps%20and%20bounds.%20Algiers%20claims%20that%20China%20was%20the%20first%20non-Arab%20country%20to%20recognise%20Algeria%E2%80%99s%20provisional%20government%20in%201958.%20China%20has%20since%20become%20the%20most%20important%20economic%20trade%20partner%20of%20Algeria%2C%20displacing%20the%20former%20colonial%20countries%20of%20France%20and%20Italy.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EArgentina%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cem%3EIndia%E2%80%99s%20stake%3A%3C%2Fem%3E%20India%20has%20had%20a%20strategic%20partnership%20with%20Argentina%20since%202019%2C%20which%20is%20a%20barometer%20of%20its%20interest%20in%20the%20country.%20Ahead%20of%20the%20BRICS%20summit%2C%20Brazilian%20President%20Luiz%20Inacio%20Lula%20da%20Silva%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reuters.com%2Fworld%2Fbrazils-lula-says-brics-not-meant-challenge-g7-us-2023-08-22%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Esupported%20Argentina%E2%80%99s%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20inclusion%20in%20the%20group.%20For%20Argentina%2C%20access%20to%20the%20New%20Development%20Bank%2C%20also%20called%20BRICS%20Bank%2C%20is%20particularly%20attractive%20as%20it%20struggles%20with%20depleted%20foreign%20reserves%2C%20high%20inflation%20and%20debt%20repayments%20to%20the%20International%20Monetary%20Fund.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EBangladesh%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cem%3EIndia%E2%80%99s%20stake%3A%3C%2Fem%3E%20For%20India%2C%20Dhaka%E2%80%99s%20candidature%20would%20be%20a%20relatively%20easy%20pick.%20Bangladesh%2C%20under%20the%20Sheikh%20Hasina%20government%2C%20has%20been%20India%E2%80%99s%20closest%20neighbour.%20While%20China%20remains%20a%20top%20donor%20and%20also%20a%20source%20of%20investment%20for%20Bangladesh%2C%20New%20Delhi%20continues%20to%20have%20substantial%20confidence%20in%20Dhaka%20%E2%80%93%20as%20long%20as%20the%20Awami%20League%20is%20at%20the%20helm.%20The%20relationship%20is%20not%20officially%20termed%20as%20a%20strategic%20one%2C%20but%20the%202022%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.pmindia.gov.in%2Fen%2Fnews_updates%2Findia-bangladesh-joint-statement-during-the-state-visit-of-pri