20the%20region.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EBelarus%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cem%3EIndia%E2%80%99s%20stake%3A%3C%2Fem%3E%20As%20Russia%E2%80%99s%20closest%20ally%20in%20Central%20Asia%20and%20also%20a%20target%20of%20Western%20sanctions%20due%20to%20the%20Ukraine%20war%2C%20it%20won%E2%80%99t%20be%20a%20surprise%20to%20expect%20Belarus%20to%20toe%20the%20anti-West%20line%20in%20BRICS.%20While%20Russia%20and%20China%20are%20likely%20to%20back%20Belarus%2C%20India%20may%20remain%20more%20ambiguous.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EBolivia%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cem%3EIndia%E2%80%99s%20stake%3A%3C%2Fem%3E%20Bolivia%20has%20been%20using%20its%20vast%20Lithium%20reserves%2C%20estimated%20to%20be%20the%20biggest%20in%20the%20world%2C%20to%20attract%20investors%20from%20large%20economies%20as%20it%20struggles%20to%20ramp%20up%20production%20on%20an%20industrial%20scale.%20Lithium-ion%20batteries%20are%20key%20components%20to%20store%20solar%2C%20wind%20and%20other%20renewable%20energy%20sources.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%202019%2C%20then%20Indian%20President%20Ram%20Nath%20Kovind%20travelled%20to%20Bolivia%2C%20where%20the%20countries%20agreed%20to%20%E2%80%9Cwork%20together%20for%20exploration%20and%20extraction%20of%20the%20vast%20Lithium%20deposits%E2%80%9D.%20Five%20years%20later%2C%20Bolivia%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reuters.com%2Fworld%2Famericas%2Fbolivia-seals-14-bln-lithium-deals-with-russias-rosatom-chinas-guoan-2023-06-29%2F%3Futm_source%3Dpocket_saves%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eannounced%20in%20June%20this%20year%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20that%20it%20has%20signed%20deals%20with%20Russian%20and%20Chinese%20firms%20worth%20%241.4%20billion%20to%20develop%20lithium%20extraction.%20While%20relations%20with%20the%20US%20were%20especially%20hostile%20under%20the%20Evo%20Morales%20presidency%2C%20there%20has%20not%20been%20substantial%20improvement%20in%20ties%20under%20Louis%20Arce%20either.%20Besides%20Russia%20and%20China%2C%20Bolivia%20has%20strong%20relations%20with%20Cuba%2C%20Iran%20and%20Venezuela.%20Bolivia%20had%20abstained%20from%20voting%20in%20UN%20resolutions%20regarding%20Russia%E2%80%99s%20invasion%20of%20Ukraine.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3ECuba%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cem%3EIndia%E2%80%99s%20stake%3A%3C%2Fem%3E%20India%E2%80%99s%20historical%20rapport%20with%20Cuba%20has%20endured%2C%20although%20the%20degree%20of%20intimacy%20has%20waned%20compared%20to%20the%20peak%20of%20the%20relationship%20during%20the%20NAM%20era.%20In%20this%20context%2C%20India%E2%80%99s%20priorities%20might%20be%20swayed%20more%20by%20the%20sensitivities%20of%20the%20US%20%E2%80%93%20which%20has%20recently%20raised%20an%20alarm%20about%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Fus%2Fus-confirms-china-has-had-a-spy-base-in-cuba-since-at-least-2019%2Farticleshow%2F100914034.cms%3Ffrom%3Dmdr%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EChina%E2%80%99s%20spying%20operations%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20in%20Cuba%2C%20which%20was%20vociferously%20denied%20by%20the%20latter%20two.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EEgypt%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cem%3EIndia%E2%80%99s%20stake%3A%3C%2Fem%3E%20With%20relations%20with%20Egypt%20having%20been%20rekindled%20recently%2C%20India%20will%20certainly%20back%20Cairo.%20The%20choice%20is%20made%20easier%20as%20India%20and%20Egypt%20also%20signed%20a%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findianexpress.com%2Farticle%2Findia%2Findia-egypt-sign-pact-on-strategic-partnership-as-modi-el-sisi-hold-talks-8685999%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Estrategic%20partnership%20earlier%20this%20year%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%20But%2C%20with%20a%20number%20of%20other%20applicants%20from%20the%20Gulf%20with%20whom%20India%20has%20a%20strategic%20partnership%2C%20it%20may%20not%20be%20easy%20for%20New%20Delhi%20to%20give%20its%20backing%20to%20all%20of%20them%20at%20once.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F06%2F25200857%2Fimage-1086.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221073%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F06%2F25200857%2Fimage-1086.png%201073w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F06%2F25200857%2Fimage-1086-300x143.png%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F06%2F25200857%2Fimage-1086-1024x490.png%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-660084%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22513%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EPrime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi%20and%20Egyptian%20President%20Abdel%20Fattah%20El-Sisi.%20Photo%3A%20Twitter%40narendramodi%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EEthiopia%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cem%3EIndia%E2%80%99s%20stake%3A%3C%2Fem%3E%20India%20has%20always%20looked%20at%20Ethiopia%20as%20one%20of%20the%20key%20African%20countries%2C%20especially%20as%20the%20seat%20of%20the%20African%20Union%20(AU).%20It%20has%20also%20supported%20Ethiopia%E2%80%99s%20position%20at%20the%20UN%20on%20issues%20from%20the%20Tigray%20crisis%20to%20the%20controversy%20over%20the%20Grand%20Ethiopian%20Renaissance%20Dam.%20With%20India%20advocating%20for%20greater%20AU%20representation%20in%20the%20G-20%20and%20UN%2C%20it%20would%20make%20all%20the%20positive%20noises%2C%20even%20with%20Ethiopia%20having%20also%20deep%20ties%20with%20China.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EHonduras%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cem%3EIndia%E2%80%99s%20stake%3A%3C%2Fem%3E%20Earlier%20this%20year%2C%20the%20central%20American%20state%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindu.com%2Fnews%2Finternational%2Fhonduras-opens-embassy-in-china-after-breaking-off-ties-with-taiwan%2Farticle66956968.ece%3Futm_source%3Dpocket_saves%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eestablished%20formal%20ties%20with%20China%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20after%20breaking%20diplomatic%20relations%20with%20Taiwan.%20Soon%20after%2C%20Honduran%20President%20Xiomara%20Castro%20travelled%20to%20China%20for%20a%20six-day%20visit%20and%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.globaltimes.cn%2Fpage%2F202306%2F1292328.shtml%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Epublicly%20talked%20about%20applying%20for%20BRICS%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%20India%20has%20minimal%20engagement%20which%20is%20borne%20out%20by%20its%20administering%20diplomatic%20relations%20with%20Honduras%20through%20its%20embassy%20in%20Guatemala.%20Similarly%2C%20Honduras%E2%80%99%20embassy%20in%20Kuwait%20is%20accredited%20to%20the%20Indian%20government.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EIndonesia%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EI%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cem%3Endia%E2%80%99s%20stake%3A%3C%2Fem%3E%20With%20the%20size%20of%20its%20economy%20and%20its%20strategic%20position%2C%20Indonesia%20has%20long%20been%20cited%20as%20an%20ideal%20candidate%20for%20an%20expanded%20BRICS.%20New%20Delhi%20has%20been%20judicious%20in%20courting%20Indonesia%2C%20the%20largest%20economy%20in%20ASEAN%2C%20over%20the%20years.%20India%20had%20signed%20a%20strategic%20partnership%20with%20Indonesia%20as%20early%20as%202005%2C%20which%20was%20upgraded%20to%20a%20comprehensive%20strategic%20partnership%20in%202018.%20Jakarta%20has%20also%20similarly%20accommodated%20India%E2%80%99s%20requests%2C%20whether%20to%20change%20the%20G-20%20hosting%20year%20or%20facilitate%20the%20UNSC%20listing%20of%20Maulana%20Masood%20Azhar.%20It%20also%20did%20not%20make%20too%20much%20of%20a%20diplomatic%20fuss%20over%20the%20criminal%20cases%20that%20were%20lodged%20by%20police%20in%20India%20against%20Indonesian%20nationals%20who%20arrived%20for%20the%20gathering%20of%20the%20Tablighi%20Jamaat%20at%20the%20beginning%20of%20the%20COVID-19%20pandemic%20in%202020.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EIran%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cem%3EIndia%E2%80%99s%20stake%3A%3C%2Fem%3E%20India%E2%80%99s%20relationship%20with%20Iran%20has%20through%20its%20ups%20and%20downs%20%E2%80%93%20especially%20after%20the%20US-India%20nuclear%20deal%20and%20imposition%20of%20sanctions%20on%20Tehran.%20India%20had%20cut%20down%20its%20crude%20purchases%20from%20Iran%20and%20tried%20to%20devise%20payment%20mechanisms%20to%20circumvent%20sanctions%20over%20the%20years.%20Iran%20remains%20a%20highly%20crucial%20partner%20due%20to%20its%20proximity%20to%20Central%20Asia%20and%20its%20borders%20with%20Afghanistan%20and%20Pakistan.%20A%20determined%20candidate%2C%20Iranian%20President%20Ebrahim%20Raisi%20spoke%20with%20the%20Indian%20PM%20about%20the%20expansion%20on%20the%20phone%20ahead%20of%20the%20BRICS%20summit.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAn%20Iranian%20membership%20in%20BRICS%20would%20certainly%20be%20seen%20as%20cocking%20a%20snook%20at%20the%20West%20by%20Russia%20and%20China%2C%20just%20as%20it%20was%20perceived%20when%20the%20country%20was%20granted%20entry%20to%20the%20Shanghai%20Cooperation%20Organisation%20(SCO).%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EKazakhstan%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cem%3EIndia%E2%80%99s%20stake%3A%3C%2Fem%3E%20Kazakhstan%20remains%20India%E2%80%99s%20largest%20trading%20partner%20in%20Central%20Asia%20and%20is%20key%20to%20its%20plans%20for%20closer%20connectivity%20with%20the%20region.%20While%20China%E2%80%99s%20Belt%20and%20Road%20Initiative%20has%20a%20strong%20presence%20in%20the%20Central%20Asian%20nation%2C%20there%20have%20also%20been%20domestic%20concerns%20about%20its%20large%20footprints.%20While%20Kazakhstan%20has%20always%20been%20a%20reliable%20ally%20for%20Russia%2C%20the%20Ukraine%20war%20has%20seen%20a%20shift%20as%20it%20has%20distanced%20itself%20from%20the%20Kremlin%20on%20key%20issues%20like%20territorial%20integrity%20and%20non-recognition%20of%20Donetsk%20and%20Luhansk.%20Since%20the%20Ukraine%20war%2C%20Kazakhstan%20has%20deepened%20ties%20with%20China%20and%20even%20looked%20beyond%20to%20strengthen%20relations%20with%20the%20European%20Union.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EKuwait%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cem%3EIndia%E2%80%99s%20stake%3A%3C%2Fem%3E%20There%20has%20always%20been%20potential%20to%20improve%20ties%20with%20Kuwait%2C%20but%20as%20experts%20have%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.google.co.in%2Fbooks%2Fedition%2FPersian_Gulf_2021_22%2F-LCbEAAAQBAJ%3Fhl%3Den%26gbpv%3D1%26dq%3Dindia%2527s%2Bpolitical%2Brelations%2Bwith%2Bkuwait%2Birritants%26pg%3DPA250%26printsec%3Dfrontcover%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eobserved%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%3Cspan%3E%20it%20has%20not%20kept%20pace%20with%20India%E2%80%99s%20growing%20engagement%20with%20the%20Gulf%20Cooperation%20Council%20(GCC)%20countries.%20There%20have%20also%20been%20sensitivities%20when%20Bahraini%20social%20media%20users%20had%20flagged%20Islamophobic%20tweets%20by%20Indian%20residents%20in%20the%20Gulf.%20There%20also%20had%20been%20a%20diplomatic%20protest%20over%20the%20remarks%20of%20a%20BJP%20spokesperson%20related%20to%20Prophet%20Mohammed.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3ENigeria%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cem%3EIndia%E2%80%99s%20stake%3A%3C%2Fem%3E%20Nigeria%2C%20Africa%E2%80%99s%20most%20populous%20nation%2C%20was%20the%20seventh%20largest%20source%20of%20oil%20for%20India%20globally%20and%20the%20top%20destination%20for%20crude%20from%20the%20African%20continent.%20In%20fact%2C%20Nigeria%20is%20India%E2%80%99s%20top%20African%20trade%20partner.%20During%20Manmohan%20Singh%E2%80%99s%20visit%20to%20Abuja%20in%20October%202007%2C%20India%20and%20Nigeria%20declared%20a%20%E2%80%9Cstrategic%20partnership%E2%80%9D.%20Nevertheless%2C%20just%20like%20in%20other%20parts%20of%20Africa%2C%20China%20has%20an%20edge%20not%20just%20over%20India%20but%20other%20Western%20countries%20in%20comprehensive%20influence.%20During%20the%20recent%20presidential%20election%20earlier%20this%20year%2C%20the%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fasia.nikkei.com%2FPolitics%2FInternational-relations%2FChina-looms-large-over-Nigeria-s-presidential-election%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eopposition%20had%20accused%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20the%20ruling%20party%20of%20using%20Chinese%20technology%20for%20surveillance.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EPalestine%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cem%3EIndia%E2%80%99s%20stake%3A%3C%2Fem%3E%20Although%20India%20has%20usually%20backed%20Palestine%E2%80%99s%20participation%20in%20multilateral%20platforms%2C%20it%E2%80%99s%20uncertain%20whether%20Palestine%20will%20fulfil%20the%20economic%20requirements%20that%20might%20be%20set%20to%20attract%20bigger%20economies%20or%20those%20with%20more%20diplomatic%20influence.%20Traditionally%2C%20BRICS%20has%20supported%20Palestine%20in%20the%20conflict%20with%20Israel%20but%20it%20has%20not%20been%20a%20major%20player.%20With%20China%20wading%20into%20the%20long-standing%20dispute%20flush%20from%20the%20success%20of%20its%20Iran-Saudi%20rapprochement%2C%20it%20will%20certainly%20have%20more%20leverage%20with%20the%20nascent%20quasi-state.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3ESaudi%20Arabia%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cspan%3EIndia%E2%80%99s%20stake%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cem%3E%3A%3C%2Fem%3E%20With%20Saudi%20Arabia%20diversifying%20its%20diplomatic%20relationship%20away%20from%20the%20West%2C%20it%20joined%20the%20SCO%20as%20a%20dialogue%20partner.%20Therefore%2C%20its%20move%20to%20apply%20for%20BRICS%20would%20be%20in%20line%20with%20its%20current%20trajectory%20%E2%80%93%20and%20also%20give%20it%20access%20to%20emerging%20markets.%20India%20signed%20a%20strategic%20partnership%20in%202010%20and%20created%20a%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.mea.gov.in%2Fbilateral-documents.htm%3Fdtl%2F31072%2FIndiaSaudi%2BArabia%2BJoint%2BStatement%2Bduring%2Bthe%2BState%2BVisit%2Bof%2BHis%2BRoyal%2BHighness%2Bthe%2BCrown%2BPrince%2Bof%2BSaudi%2BArabia%2Bto%2BIndia%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Estrategic%20partnership%20council%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20in%202019%2C%20which%20indicates%20the%20concentrated%20effort%20by%20New%20Delhi%20to%20woo%20the%20Gulf%20kingdom.%20It%E2%80%99s%20very%20unlikely%20that%20Saudi%20Arabia%E2%80%99s%20application%20will%20face%20any%20objections%20%E2%80%93%20unless%20it%E2%80%99s%20about%20the%20number%20of%20countries%20from%20a%20certain%20region.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2019%2F02%2F19221325%2Fmbs-modi.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221024%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2019%2F02%2F19221325%2Fmbs-modi.jpg%201024w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2019%2F02%2F19221325%2Fmbs-modi-300x200.jpg%20300w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-339269%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22682%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EPM%20Modi%20receives%20Saudi%20crown%20prince%20Mohammed%20bin%20Salman.%20Credit%3A%20Twitter%2FRaveesh%20Kumar%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3ESenegal%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cem%3EIndia%E2%80%99s%20stake%3A%3C%2Fem%3E%20In%202021%2C%20Senegal%20hosted%20the%20Forum%20on%20China-Africa%20Cooperation%20(FOCAC)%2C%20which%20indicated%20the%20commitment%20of%20the%20West%20African%20state%20to%20ties%20with%20Beijing.%20India%20had%20also%20wooed%20Senegal%2C%20which%20held%20an%20AU%20presidency%20last%20year%2C%20when%20the%20Indian%20Vice%20President%20visited%20Senegal%20and%20signed%20MoUs.%20But%20China%E2%80%99s%20influence%20is%20clear.%20Senegal%20was%20among%20the%20eight%20African%20members%20that%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fdiplomacy%2Fat-unhrc-india-abstains-on-resolution-on-xinjiang-rejected-by-slim-margin%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Evoted%20against%20a%20resolution%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20that%20sought%20a%20debate%20on%20the%20treatment%20of%20Uyghurs%20in%20the%20UN%20human%20rights%20council%20last%20October.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EThailand%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cem%3EIndia%E2%80%99s%20stake%3A%3C%2Fem%3E%20Both%20countries%20view%20each%20other%20as%20the%20%E2%80%98gateway%E2%80%99%20to%20their%20respective%20regions.%20While%20there%20have%20been%20political%20irritants%2C%20there%20are%20also%20challenges%20due%20to%20the%20slow%20progress%20of%20connectivity%20projects%20and%20common%20concerns%20about%20Myanmar.%20Bangkok%20walks%20a%20careful%20balancing%20act%20between%20the%20US%20and%20China%2C%20taking%20a%20more%20neutral%20position%20on%20policy%20issues.%20In%20February%20this%20year%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.un.org%2Fen%2Fstory%2F2023%2F02%2F1133847%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EThailand%20voted%20in%20favour%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20of%20the%20UN%20General%20Assembly%20resolution%20calling%20for%20an%20end%20to%20the%20Ukraine%20war%20on%20the%20one-year%20anniversary%20of%20its%20inception.%20This%20was%20a%20change%20from%20its%20earlier%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bangkokpost.com%2Fworld%2F2413705%2Fthailand-abstains-in-un-vote-against-putin-land-grab%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eabstention%20on%20another%20UNGA%20resolution%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20on%20Ukraine%20last%20year.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EThe%20UAE%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cem%3EIndia%E2%80%99s%20stake%3A%3C%2Fem%3E%20After%20the%20Abu%20Dhabi%20Crown%20Prince%20visited%20India%20as%20the%20chief%20guest%20for%20India%E2%80%99s%20Republic%20Day%20celebrations%20in%202017%2C%20India%20and%20the%20UAE%20upgraded%20their%20relationship%20to%20a%20%E2%80%9CComprehensive%20Strategic%20Partnership.%E2%80%9D%20This%20stands%20as%20one%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20most%20robust%20partnerships%20in%20the%20region.%20In%202021%2C%20India%20participated%20in%20a%20quadrilateral%20meeting%20alongside%20the%20UAE%2C%20which%20has%20since%20evolved%20into%20the%20%E2%80%98i2u2%E2%80%99%20grouping.%20Demonstrating%20a%20practical%20foreign%20policy%2C%20the%20UAE%20normalised%20relations%20with%20Israel%20through%20the%20Abraham%20Accords%2C%20while%20also%20doubling%20the%20trade%20volume%20with%20China%20compared%20to%20the%20US.%20India%E2%80%99s%20political%20differences%20with%20UAE%2C%20just%20like%20with%20Saudi%20Arabia%2C%20is%20over%20the%20role%20of%20Iran%20and%20China%20%E2%80%93%20but%20that%20has%20not%20been%20a%20hindrance%20to%20expanding%20ties.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EVenezuela%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cem%3EIndia%E2%80%99s%20stake%3A%3C%2Fem%3E%20The%20Latin%20American%20state%20had%20been%20a%20major%20source%20of%20oil%20for%20India%20but%20imports%20were%20drastically%20reduced%20after%20the%20US%20%E2%80%93%20under%20the%20Donald%20Trump%20administration%20%E2%80%93%20imposed%20unilateral%20sanctions%20on%20Venezuela.%20The%20country%E2%80%99s%20vice%20president%20Delcy%20Rodr%C3%ADguez%20was%20in%20India%20earlier%20this%20month%20when%20she%20claimed%20that%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20largest%20reserve%20of%20the%20planet%20at%20the%20service%20of%20this%20important%20block%20(BRICS)%E2%80%9D.%20Over%20the%20years%2C%20Venezuela%20has%20been%20diplomatically%20active%20at%20multilateral%20forums%20with%20its%20avowed%20anti-West%20position.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhile%20India%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20have%20any%20strategic%20partnership%20with%20Latin%20American%20applicants%20besides%20Argentina%2C%20New%20Delhi%20could%20very%20well%20give%20the%20lead%20in%20the%20region%20to%20Brazil%20%E2%80%93%20which%20has%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reuters.com%2Farticle%2Fbrazil-summit-brics-idAFS0N37802A%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eextended%20support%20to%20Venezuela%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EVietnam%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cem%3EIndia%E2%80%99s%20stake%3A%3C%2Fem%3E%20This%20is%20an%20easy%20decision%20for%20New%20Delhi%20since%20India%20and%20Vietnam%20signed%20a%20strategic%20partnership%20as%20early%20as%202007.%20This%20was%20elevated%20to%20a%20%E2%80%9CComprehensive%20Strategic%20Partnership%E2%80%99%20in%202016.%20China%E2%80%99s%20influence%20in%20South%20East%20Asia%20%E2%80%93%20and%20its%20presence%20in%20the%20South%20China%20Sea%20%E2%80%93%20has%20long%20been%20the%20prism%20for%20India%E2%80%99s%20long-term%20view%20of%20its%20relationship%20with%20Vietnam.%20While%20Vietnam%20has%20historically%20been%20wary%20of%20China%20and%20seeks%20to%20maintain%20a%20balance%20with%20India%2C%20it%E2%80%99s%20important%20to%20note%20that%20its%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thestar.com.my%2Faseanplus%2Faseanplus-news%2F2023%2F02%2F19%2Fvietnam-and-china-more-than-happy-to-bolster-economic-cooperation-and-improve-bilateral-relationship%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Etrade%20volume%20with%20Beijing%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20is%20approximately%2015%20times%20greater%20than%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.indembassyhanoi.gov.in%2Fnews_letter_detail%2F%3Fid%3D197%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eits%20economic%20ties%20with%20New%20Delhi%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1692844240000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F23224458%2FH20230823137024.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fdiplomacy%2Findia-brics-22-countries-expansion-stakes