ating%20their%20meat%20and%20dairy%20separately%20or%20mixing%20it%20all%20together.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20evidence%20for%20the%20meals%20comes%20from%20proteins%20found%20in%20skillfully%20made%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Farchaeologists-upper-class-bronze-age-man-who-underwent-brain-surgery-2023-2%5C%22%3EBronze%20Age%3C%2Fa%3E%20pots%20that%20were%20%26quot%3Bused%20to%20cook%20a%20large%20amount%20of%20meat%20with%20some%20milk%20that%20we%20suggest%20was%20in%20the%20form%20of%20a%20stew%2C%26quot%3B%20Shevan%20Wilkin%20told%20Insider%20in%20an%20email.%20They're%20some%20of%20the%20earliest%20known%20metal%20cooking%20cauldrons.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWilkin%20and%20Viktor%20Trifonov%20co-authored%20the%20study%2C%20which%20appeared%20in%20the%20journal%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cell.com%2Fiscience%2Ffulltext%2FS2589-0042(23)01559-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EiScience%3C%2Fa%3E%20this%20month.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EResearchers%20have%20tried%20studying%20ancient%20dietary%20habits%20from%20ceramics%20dishes%20before%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpubs.acs.org%2Fdoi%2F10.1021%2Fcen-10041-scicon4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewith%20little%20success%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20but%20Wilkin%20thinks%20the%20antimicrobial%20properties%20of%20the%20copper-alloy%20cauldrons%20helped%20preserve%20the%20ancient%20biomolecules.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20finding%20was%20incredibly%20exciting%2C%20as%20it%20opens%20the%20possibility%20of%20many%20more%20studies%20into%20the%20foods%20and%20drinks%20prepared%2C%20served%2C%20or%20consumed%20from%20metallic%20cups%2C%20bowls%2C%20or%20larger%20vessels%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3ECattle%2C%20sheep%2C%20and%20goat%20could%20have%20all%20been%20on%20the%20menu%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ETaking%20samples%20from%20seven%20copper-alloy%20cauldrons%20allowed%20the%20researchers%20to%20get%20some%20specific%20dietary%20information%20from%20proteins%20that%2C%20remarkably%2C%20still%20remained%20in%20the%20vessels%205%2C000%20years%20later.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20pots%20contained%20blood%2C%20muscle%2C%20and%20milk%20proteins%2C%20representing%20several%20different%20types%20of%20animals.%20Heat%20shock%20protein%20beta-1%2C%20abundant%20in%20muscle%20tissue%2C%20helps%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmedlineplus.gov%2Fgenetics%2Fgene%2Fhspb1%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eprotect%20cells%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20infection%20and%20inflammation.%20%3Cstrong%3E%3Cbr%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAn%20amino%20acid%20sequence%20in%20the%20tissue%20protein%20researchers%20identified%20belongs%20to%20the%20bovine%20subfamily%20or%20deer%20genus%20Cervus.%20The%20Bronze%20Age%20chefs%20could%20have%20been%20making%20cow%2C%20yak%2C%20water%20buffalo%2C%20or%20wild%20deer.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWilkin%20and%20Trifonov%20also%20found%20three%20different%20blood%20proteins%2C%20including%20one%20specific%20to%20sheep%20or%20goats.%20The%20milk%20proteins%20show%20the%20Maykop%20people%20were%20also%20getting%20their%20dairy%20from%20these%20animals.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20cauldron%20had%20both%20blood%20and%20milk%20proteins.%20The%20researchers%20said%20the%20pot's%20owners%20may%20have%20cooked%20the%20meat%20and%20dairy%20together%2C%20but%20it's%20impossible%20to%20tell%20for%20sure.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20also%20unknown%20if%20the%20stew%20contained%20grains%20or%20other%20crops.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20don't%20learn%20anything%20about%20the%20plants%20that%20they%20might%20have%20been%20cooking%20in%20there%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Farf.berkeley.edu%2Fwho-we-are%2Ffaculty-director%2Fchristine-hastorf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EChristine%20Hastorf%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20director%20of%20the%20Archaeological%20Research%20Facility%20at%20the%20University%20of%20California%2C%20Berkeley%2C%20who%20wasn't%20involved%20in%20the%20study.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20notes%20that%20stews%20often%20contain%20vegetables%2C%20but%20animal%20proteins%20are%20sturdier%20and%20more%20likely%20to%20survive.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EPart%20of%20a%20communal%20kitchen%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWilkin%20believes%20creating%20these%20pots%20would%20have%20been%20a%20complicated%20process.%20%26quot%3BThis%20is%20one%20of%20the%20earliest%20known%20cauldrons%20to%20date%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt%20would%20have%20taken%20a%20lot%20of%20knowledge%20and%20skill%20to%20make%20it.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBased%20on%20radiocarbon%20dating%2C%20the%20pots%20are%20from%20between%203%2C520%20to%203%2C350%20BCE%2C%20during%20the%20Maykop%20period%20and%20were%20found%20in%20a%20few%20burial%20sites%20east%20of%20the%20Black%20Sea.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221999%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Green%20hills%2C%20trees%2C%20and%20mountains%20are%20part%20of%20the%20landscape%20in%20the%20Maykopsky%20District%2C%20Adygea%20Republic%20in%20Russia%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64e38f09b698ac0019de3954%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221499%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20landscape%20of%20the%20Maykopsky%20District%2C%20Adygea%20Republic%2C%20Russia%2C%20near%20where%20the%20Maykop%20burials%20are%20located.%3Cp%3ESakib%20Ahmmed%2F500px%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EProcuring%20the%20necessary%20metal%20and%20finding%20someone%20skilled%20enough%20to%20craft%20the%20pot%20meant%20not%20everyone%20could%20have%20one.%20%26quot%3BThe%20cauldrons%20are%20associated%20exclusively%20with%20the%20burials%20of%20the%20elite%2C%26quot%3B%20Trifonov%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYet%20the%20capacity%20of%20the%20pots%20%E2%80%94%20the%20largest%20had%20a%20volume%20of%2070%20liters%20%E2%80%94%20indicates%20the%20Maykop%20people%20used%20them%20for%20communal