0of%20vegetables%20cost%20her%20Rs%2010%20then%2C%20up%20to%20Rs%2020-Rs%2025%20now%3B%20the%20round-trip%20fare%20to%20Girnare%20was%20Rs%2040%2C%20up%20to%20Rs%2060%20now.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EVegetable%20vendors%20in%20Lucknow%2C%20Delhi%20and%20Chandigarh%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.hindustantimes.com%2Findia-news%2Fheatwave-and-rains-cause-spike-in-vegetable-prices-across-india-tomato-at-rs-120-kg-ginger-at-rs-250kg-101688667827024.html%5C%22%3Etold%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3Cem%3EHindustan%20Times%20%3C%2Fem%3Ethat%20the%20vegetable%20prices%20increased%20between%2020%25%20and%2060%25%20in%20a%20matter%20of%20ten%20days.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20inflation%20is%20not%20new.%20In%202021%2C%20tomato%20prices%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fbusiness%2Findia-business%2Ftomato-over-rs-100%2Fkg-onion-prices-up-65-when-will-rates-come-down%2Farticleshow%2F87936863.cms%5C%22%3Ewitnessed%3C%2Fa%3E%20a%20rise%20of%20142%25.%20This%20is%20because%20states%20which%20are%20key%20suppliers%20of%20tomato%20like%20Karnataka%2C%20Andhra%20Pradesh%20and%20Maharashtra%20experienced%20above%20normal%20rainfall.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ESo%20why%20does%20food%20inflation%20appear%20to%20be%20hurting%20people%E2%80%99s%20pockets%20more%20this%20time%3F%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIncomes%20have%20not%20been%20increasing%20in%20India.%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Financial%20Express%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.financialexpress.com%2Feconomy%2Frural-recovery-subdued-real-wages-shrink-for-16th-month%2F3155712%2F%5C%22%3Ereported%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20in%20July%2C%20that%20rural%20wages%20contracted%20for%20the%2016th%20straight%20month%20up%20to%20March.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETherefore%2C%20stagnant%20wages%20coupled%20with%20increasing%20living%20costs%20have%20exacerbated%20the%20impact%20of%20inflation%20in%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20the%20first%20time%20in%2018%20years%2C%20food%20costs%20crossed%2040%25%20of%20monthly%20spends%20in%202017-18%2C%20for%20urban%20households%20in%20Maharashtra%2C%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Hindu%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindu.com%2Fbusiness%2Fshelved-2017-18-consumption-spending-survey-showed-inequality-widening-in-maharashtra%2Farticle67042208.ece%5C%22%3Ereported%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20in%20July%2C%20citing%20data%20from%20the%20National%20Statistical%20Office%E2%80%99s%202017-18%20Household%20Consumption%20Expenditure%20Survey.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20situation%20is%20worse%20for%20rural%20households%20whose%20food%20bill%20shot%20up%20to%20almost%2049%25%20of%20total%20spending%2C%20with%20that%20figure%20crossing%2060%25%20for%20the%20poorest%205%25%20of%20households%2C%20the%20report%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFurthermore%2C%20unemployment%20rates%20have%20been%20on%20the%20rise%2C%20primarily%20driven%20by%20seasonal%20joblessness%20in%20rural%20areas.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20unemployment%20rate%20jumped%20to%208.45%25%20in%20June%20from%207.68%25%20in%20the%20previous%20month%2C%20according%20to%20the%20Centre%20for%20Monitoring%20Indian%20Economy.%20It%20rose%20above%208%25%20for%20the%20third%20time%20this%20year%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Feconomy%2Fnews%2Fweak-rural-labour-market-pushes-india-s-unemployment-rate-above-8-123070300234_1.html%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EBloomberg%3C%2Fem%3E%20reported.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Feconomy%2Fis-food-inflation-in-india-driven-by-demand-or-supply%5C%22%3EIs%20Food%20Inflation%20in%20India%20Driven%20by%20Demand%20or%20Supply%3F%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EHow%20does%20food%20inflation%20affect%20the%20average%20Indian%20consumer%E2%80%99s%20cost%20of%20living%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFood%20is%20a%20fundamental%20necessity%2C%20so%20when%20food%20prices%20rise%2C%20it%20directly%20affects%20the%20daily%20expenses%20of%20households.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESince%20a%20substantial%20portion%20of%20an%20average%20Indian%20household%E2%80%99s%20budget%20is%20allocated%20to%20food%2C%20any%20increase%20in%20food%20prices%20can%20lead%20to%20a%20significant%20increase%20in%20overall%20expenses.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnd%2C%20as%20earlier%20mentioned%2C%20when%20food%20inflation%20goes%20up%2C%20purchasing%20power%20goes%20down.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20can%20also%20lead%20to%20a%20lower%20standard%20of%20living%20for%20many%20families%2C%20because%20rising%20food%20prices%20may%20lead%20families%20to%20change%20their%20consumption%20patterns.%20For%20instance%2C%20people%20may%20opt%20for%20less%20nutritious%20foods%20such%20as%20fruits%20and%20vegetables%20that%20can%20lead%20to%20long-term%20health%20issues.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENote%20that%2074.1%25%20of%20the%20Indian%20population%2C%20i.e.%20three%20in%20every%20four%20Indians%20cannot%20afford%20healthy%20food%2C%20according%20to%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.indiatoday.in%2Fdiu%2Fstory%2Fmalnutrition-in-india-global-organisations-reports-comparison-with-other-countries-2407735-2023-07-17%5C%22%3Ejoint%20report%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20FAO%2C%20IFAD%2C%20UNICEF%2C%20WEP%20and%20WHO.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EAre%20there%20social%20consequences%20of%20persistent%20food%20inflation%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20high%20inflation%20rate%20increases%20poverty%20and%20inequality.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20given%20amount%20of%20money%20buys%20less%20as%20prices%20rise.%20So%20either%20the%20individual%20buys%20less%20than%20earlier%20or%20has%20to%20shell%20out%20more%20money%20to%20buy%20the%20same%20amount%20as%20earlier.%20In%20the%20former%20case%2C%20the%20living%20standard%20of%20the%20individual%20falls.%20In%20the%20latter%20case%2C%20the%20savings%20of%20the%20individual%20decline.%20Either%20way%2C%20individuals%20lose%20unless%20their%20incomes%20rise%20at%20least%20at%20the%20same%20rate%20as%20the%20price%20rise.%20This%20is%20called%20indexation%20of%20incomes%20to%20prices%2C%20retired%20Jawaharlal%20Nehru%20University%20professor%20Arun%20Kumar%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Feconomy%2Fa-decline-in-inflation-is-no-comfort-for-the-majority%5C%22%3Eexplained%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20this%20piece%20written%20for%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnd%20India%20has%20extreme%20inequality.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAbout%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fedition.cnn.com%2Finteractive%2F2017%2F10%2Fworld%2Fi-on-india-income-gap%2F%5C%22%3E60%25%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20nearly%201.3%20billion%20people%3C%2Fa%3E%20live%20on%20less%20than%20%243.10%20(approximately%20Rs%20250)%20a%20day%2C%20the%20World%20Bank%E2%80%99s%20median%20poverty%20line.%20And%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Fpovertydata.worldbank.org%2Fpoverty%2Fcountry%2FIND%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E21%25%2C%20or%20more%20than%20250%20million%20people%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20survive%20on%20less%20than%20%242%20(approximately%20Rs%20166)%20a%20day.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20the%20richest%2010%25%20in%20India%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Feconomy%2Finequality-exacerbated-in-india-during-covid-19-bottom-50s-income-contracted-report%5C%22%3Econtrols%3C%2Fa%3E%2080%25%20of%20the%20nation%E2%80%99s%20wealth%2C%20according%20to%20a%202017%20report%20published%20by%20Oxfam%2C%20an%20international%20confederation%20of%20agencies%20fighting%20poverty.%20And%20the%20top%201%25%20owns%2058%25%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20wealth.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPut%20simply%2C%20in%20India%2C%20the%20wealth%20of%2016%20people%20is%20equal%20to%20the%20wealth%20of%20600%20million%20people.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%202021%2C%20the%3Cem%3E%20Times%20of%20India%3C%2Fem%3E%20cited%20a%20report%20saying%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Freadersblog%2Fspot-on%2Fthe-abundance-of-fruits-and-vegetables-39185%2F%5C%22%3Eper%20capita%20consumption%20of