ung%20boy%2C%20cheeky%20and%20in%20no%20way%20averse%20to%20the%20usual%20pranks%20and%20fights.%20You%20also%20say%20you%20had%20a%20loving%2C%20tenderly%20caring%20mother%20and%20a%20wonderful%20father.%20So%20was%20the%20young%20Zubin%20naughty%2C%20and%20was%20he%20pampered%3F%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EZM%3A%3C%2Fb%3E%3Cspan%3E%20I%20don%E2%80%99t%20think%20so.%20My%20brother%20was%20naughty%2C%20the%20young%20one.%20He%20gave%20my%20mother%20a%20bad%20time%20when%20he%20was%20very%20young.%20Later%20on%20he%20changed.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBut%20tell%20me%2C%20did%20I%20put%20on%20some%20decent%20clothes%20after%20that%3F%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EKT%3A%3C%2Fb%3E%3Cspan%3E%20You%20did!%20I%20mean%20you%20said%20give%20me%2020%20minutes%2C%20and%20you%E2%80%99d%20had%20a%20shave%2C%20you%E2%80%99d%20had%20a%20bath%20and%20you%20came%20smelling%20of%20the%20most%20magnificent%20aftershave%20because%20I%20remember%20the%20cameraman%20said%20to%20you%20sir%20you%20smell%20good.%20%5BLaughter%5D%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EZM%3A%3C%2Fb%3E%3Cspan%3E%20Really!%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EKT%3A%3C%2Fb%3E%3Cspan%3E%20So%20you%20were%20the%20goody%20goody%20in%20the%20family%3F%20You%20were%20mummy%E2%80%99s%20pet%3F%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EZM%3A%3C%2Fb%3E%3Cspan%3E%20I%20wouldn%E2%80%99t%20say%20that.%20You%20ask%20my%20brother%20that.%20He%20wouldn%E2%80%99t%20agree.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EKT%3A%3C%2Fb%3E%3Cspan%3E%20You%20describe%20your%20family%20as%20an%20old-fashioned%20Parsi%20family.%20At%20another%20point%20in%20your%20autobiography%2C%20you%20call%20it%20a%20traditional%20Parsi%20family.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EZM%3A%3C%2Fb%3E%3Cspan%3E%20That%E2%80%99s%20absolutely%20true.%20That%20had%20to%20do%20a%20lot%20with%20my%20grandparents%20too.%20Every%20night%20after%20dinner%2C%20my%20grandfather%20had%20my%20brother%20and%20myself%2C%20and%20he%20taught%20us%20our%20prayers%20and%20he%20taught%20us%20arithmetic.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EKT%3A%3C%2Fb%3E%3Cspan%3E%20And%20are%20you%20good%20at%20it%3F%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EZM%3A%3C%2Fb%3E%3Cspan%3E%20Yeah%2C%20in%20those%20days%20I%20could%20say%20my%2017%20times%20tables%2C%20my%2019%20times%20tables%2C%20and%20he%20was%20that%20typical%20Parsi%20educated%2C%20counting%20on%20his%20fingers%2C%20and%20I%20still%20only%20counted%20Gujarati.%20I%20can%E2%80%99t%20do%20it%20any%20other%20way.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EKT%3A%3C%2Fb%3E%3Cspan%3E%20That%20is%20terrific.%20What%20is%2024%20in%20Gujarati%3F%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EZM%3A%3C%2Fb%3E%3Cspan%3E%20That%20came%20from%20my%20grandfather.%20My%20father%20taught%20me%20music%20and%20taught%20me%20to%20appreciate%20music%2C%20because%20he%20sat%20with%20me%20on%20a%20daily%20basis%20also%2C%20and%20we%20would%20play%20records.%20He%20had%20a%20wonderful%20collection%2C%20so%20when%20I%20went%20to%20Vienna%2C%20I%20knew%20a%20lot%20of%20music%20that%20I%20had%20heard%20at%20home.%20I%20knew%20more%20than%20most%20of%20the%20students%20in%20my%20class%20because%20I%20had%20heard%20these%20recordings%20of%20Toscanini%20and%20Furtwangler%20and%20Stokowski.%20The%20records%20in%20those%20days%20were%20terrible%20sounding%2C%20but%20their%20Tempe%2C%20the%20speed%20of%20the%20music%2C%20that%20was%20correct.%20I%20heard%20from%20my%20youth%2C%20and%20the%20first%20time%20I%20heard%20an%20orchestra%20in%20Vienna%20I%20thought%20my%20ears%20popped%20open%2C%20I%20had%20never%20heard%20anything%20like%20that.%20So%20there%20was%20quite%20an%20evolution%20in%20my%20hearing%20and%20I%20that%20became%20my%20emblem%2C%20my%20axiom%2C%20all%20my%20life.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EKT%3A%3C%2Fb%3E%3Cspan%3E%20I%20want%20very%20much%20to%20talk%20to%20you%20about%20your%20