ure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWithout%20any%20farming%20background%2C%20Ashwin%20started%20to%20grow%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F258493%2Fengineer-solar-powered-hydroponic-growing-unit-automated-fodder-production-energy-efficient-farmers%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Egreen%20fodder%20%3C%2Fa%3Eon%20the%20500%20sq%20ft%20of%20land%20in%20Pune.%20Today%2C%20he%20harvests%20500%20kilos%20of%20green%20fodder%20daily%20to%20feed%20the%20105%20cows%20and%20goats%20on%20his%20farm.%20He%20also%20set%20up%20a%20research%20lab%20%E2%80%98Scientific%20Hydroponics%E2%80%99%20to%20introduce%20farmers%20to%20the%20benefits%20of%20hydroponics%20farming.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EChanging%20the%20game%20for%20Indian%20farmers%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAshwin%20points%20out%20that%20Indian%20farmers%20lack%20access%20to%20green%20fodder%20because%20it%20requires%20large%20tracts%20of%20land%20and%20gallons%20of%20water.%20%E2%80%9CIn%20states%20like%20Haryana%2C%20Maharashtra%2C%20Jharkhand%2C%20Odisha%2C%20and%20Tamil%20Nadu%2C%20farmers%20already%20lack%20sufficient%20water%20for%20irrigation.%20If%20a%20farmer%20owns%20800%20cows%2C%20they%20have%20to%20reserve%2060%20acres%20of%20land%20to%20grow%20green%20fodder.%20That%20means%20they%20cannot%20grow%20any%20other%20crop%20on%20this%20land%2C%20which%20is%20not%20economical%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CBut%20with%20hydroponics%2C%20we%20can%20reduce%20the%20area%20and%20water%20requirements.%20With%20a%20one-tonne%20unit%20that%20can%20be%20installed%20in%20a%201%2C000-sq%20ft%20area%2C%20a%20farmer%20can%20save%20at%20least%20seven%20acres%20of%20land.%20This%20land%20can%20be%20utilised%20to%20grow%20other%20crops.%20Using%20hydroponics%2C%20farmers%20can%20harvest%20one%20kilo%20of%20green%20fodder%20by%20utilising%20just%201.5%20litres%20of%20water%20while%20saving%2099%20percent%20of%2